    "result": {"data":{"doc":{"id":"967ab7f2-ec53-561d-a0d0-2347d4b65606","html":"<p>When you install using <code class=\"language-text\">npm</code> a package into your <code class=\"language-text\">node_modules</code> folder, or also globally, how do you use it in your Node.js code?</p>\n<p>Say you install <code class=\"language-text\">lodash</code>, the popular JavaScript utility library, using</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">npm</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span> lodash</code></pre></div>\n<p>This is going to install the package in the local <code class=\"language-text\">node_modules</code> folder.</p>\n<p>To use it in your code, you just need to import it into your program using <code class=\"language-text\">require</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> _ <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">require</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'lodash'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>What if your package is an executable?</p>\n<p>In this case, it will put the executable file under the <code class=\"language-text\">node_modules/.bin/</code> folder.</p>\n<p>One easy way to demonstrate this is <a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/cowsay\">cowsay</a>.</p>\n<p>The cowsay package provides a command line program that can be executed to make a cow say something (and other animals as well ðŸ¦Š).</p>\n<p>When you install the package using <code class=\"language-text\">npm install cowsay</code>, it will install itself and a few dependencies in the <code class=\"language-text\">node_modules</code> folder:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/b245c50f5080dae16a2525fae0ba2c91/d2c2a/node_modules-content.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 58.78378378378378%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"The node_modules folder content\"\n        title=\"The node_modules folder content\"\n        src=\"/static/b245c50f5080dae16a2525fae0ba2c91/fcda8/node_modules-content.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/b245c50f5080dae16a2525fae0ba2c91/12f09/node_modules-content.png 148w,\n/static/b245c50f5080dae16a2525fae0ba2c91/e4a3f/node_modules-content.png 295w,\n/static/b245c50f5080dae16a2525fae0ba2c91/fcda8/node_modules-content.png 590w,\n/static/b245c50f5080dae16a2525fae0ba2c91/efc66/node_modules-content.png 885w,\n/static/b245c50f5080dae16a2525fae0ba2c91/d2c2a/node_modules-content.png 929w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>There is a hidden <code class=\"language-text\">.bin</code> folder, which contains symbolic links to the cowsay binaries:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/99830aefa055e247397de544ad7b7744/d2c2a/binary-files.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 38.513513513513516%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"The binary files\"\n        title=\"The binary files\"\n        src=\"/static/99830aefa055e247397de544ad7b7744/fcda8/binary-files.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/99830aefa055e247397de544ad7b7744/12f09/binary-files.png 148w,\n/static/99830aefa055e247397de544ad7b7744/e4a3f/binary-files.png 295w,\n/static/99830aefa055e247397de544ad7b7744/fcda8/binary-files.png 590w,\n/static/99830aefa055e247397de544ad7b7744/efc66/binary-files.png 885w,\n/static/99830aefa055e247397de544ad7b7744/d2c2a/binary-files.png 929w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>How do you execute those?</p>\n<p>You can of course type <code class=\"language-text\">./node_modules/.bin/cowsay</code> to run it, and it works, but <code class=\"language-text\">npx</code>, included in the recent versions of <code class=\"language-text\">npm</code> (since 5.2), is a much better option. You just run:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">npx cowsay</code></pre></div>\n<p>and <code class=\"language-text\">npx</code> will find the package location.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ad4f3d3a7464bb0f8a2845fe8e6588c2/d2c2a/cow-say.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 55.4054054054054%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Cow says something\"\n        title=\"Cow says something\"\n        src=\"/static/ad4f3d3a7464bb0f8a2845fe8e6588c2/fcda8/cow-say.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ad4f3d3a7464bb0f8a2845fe8e6588c2/12f09/cow-say.png 148w,\n/static/ad4f3d3a7464bb0f8a2845fe8e6588c2/e4a3f/cow-say.png 295w,\n/static/ad4f3d3a7464bb0f8a2845fe8e6588c2/fcda8/cow-say.png 590w,\n/static/ad4f3d3a7464bb0f8a2845fe8e6588c2/efc66/cow-say.png 885w,\n/static/ad4f3d3a7464bb0f8a2845fe8e6588c2/d2c2a/cow-say.png 929w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>","tableOfContents":"","frontmatter":{"title":"How to use or execute a package installed using npm","description":"How to include and use in your code a package installed in your node_modules folder"},"fields":{"slug":"how-to-use-or-execute-a-package-installed-using-npm","authors":["flaviocopes"," MylesBorins"," fhemberger"," LaRuaNa"," ahmadawais"]}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"how-to-use-or-execute-a-package-installed-using-npm","next":{"slug":"the-package-json-guide","title":"The package.json guide"},"previous":{"slug":"where-does-npm-install-the-packages","title":"Where does npm install the packages?"},"relativePath":"0018-how-to-use-npm-package/index.md","navigationData":{"null":[{"title":"mock","slug":"/blog/0000/00/00/mock","section":null}],"Quick Start":[{"title":"Introduction to Node.js","slug":"introduction-to-nodejs","section":"Quick Start"},{"title":"A brief history of Node.js","slug":"a-brief-history-of-nodejs","section":"Quick Start"},{"title":"How to install No